description: This project is developed for the CSULB Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) club. As part of the Data Acquisition subsystem, our mission is to collect and analyze vital trends for each car component during the race. The web app serves as a data visualizer, enabling engineers to visually observe trends through multiline graphs and explore the relationships between different subsystems.
note: MVP built but currently in development to finish upload feature, and password lock. Data will take around 30 seconds to load since backend service is hosted on a free tier plan

description: This project won the Best Google Cloud Hack 2023 during a Google sponsored hackathon. Fast Tracker is a tool that leverages QR codes to streamline the laborious process of taking attendance by 89% (14 seconds to 1.5 seconds).
note: If testing out live code, I recommend having two seperate devices. One device to scan the QR code, and another device to generate the QR code. 'test' is the id used for both attendee and volunteer user for demonstration purposes. See video for more information

description: A full-stack web application (MERN) built for the BeachHacks organization that tracks the popularity of events and workshops hosted by the organization. The data was used by the data analysis team to generate a report that will be used to make improvements to future events and workshops
note: Repository has been archived and API endpoints has been removed but front-end is still available.

description: A desktop game built with a team of four indie developers. It's a 2D pixel art game about a sentient sunflower attempting to escape a cursed flowershop!
note: The game can be played by pressing the "Run Game" button! Playing the game will have music and sound and lower the volume if necessary :). If you're interested in seeing more games we developed, press the "See Live" button!
